I’ve heard a new music hall has been set up lately at HKCU with a grant from the arts faculty. The government has awarded my friend Josh a forty five thousand dollar study grant to study engineering there. His elder brother has received a ninety one thousand five hundred dollar grant for research on driverless cars. His younger brother is applying for a research grant for stem cell research whereas his elder sister is studying computer science there. Last Monday after supper she hurried back home 🏡 I asked “what’s all the hurry for?” It turns out that the money for her study grant will dry up soon in which case she won’t be able to continue her studies. That’s why she’s in a desperate hurry to find a job. In addition, I lent a textbook to her who said she’d let me have it back next week but I said “that’s ok. There isn’t any great hurry.” His younger sister who’s a concierage feels she’s made the wrong career decision. I said “why not wipe the slate clean and start over in a different career?” Josh too suggested her to study a degree course and start with a clean slate. She blames her bad career decision on josh. I said “let’s just wipe the slate clean. It’s over” She blames him for convincing her to become a concierage. Well that’s the way the cookie crumbles. His father is a physics professor who’s currently solving a notoriously difficult math question for all he’s worth. Hopefully he’ll find an answer to it soon. Besides physics he’s also an avid football fan. His favourite team Barcelona is currently top of the league while Milan is bottom of the league. Rome is lying fourth in the league this year. The league championship is the opportunity for the best teams in the league to strut their stuff.
